result.name: Mikasaya Sushi Restaurant

reviews.text: High quality and good service

My Japanese friend recommended it.
The sashimi is awesome! Sushi is good but isn’t the best in town;) 
Expensive and the service could be a lot better.
Very good Japanese food and Sake.

High quality sashimi and sushi, very fresh and a lot of variety. Masterfully prepared by the Japanese chef, Motoyama-san, who has worked at the location for at least a decade. Motsunabe (beef intestine hotpot, which requires advanced ordering) and some other Fukuokan specialities (hakata fried chicken, seared mentaiko) also served there (chef hails from Fukuoka). Highly recommend the omakase.
very nice sushi rice and coffee

result.name: 三笠屋

reviews.text: High quality and good service
這是廚師發板的日本餐廳，日本老闆很年輕但是有一双巧手製作料理，無論是壽司，秘製醬汁，菜餚款式，海鮮等都很新鮮好吃。餐廳主要的客人都是日本人; 有酒水提供， 前來進餐可預先致電訂坐壽司枱，能與廚師溝通一下， 讓他知道你對食物的偏好。

My Japanese friend recommended it.
The sashimi is awesome! Sushi is good but isn’t the best in town;) 
Expensive and the service could be a lot better.
餐點好美味，用餐環境簡潔高雅，😊

高級日本料理を出す店です。
ネタは新鮮で味は保証できます。

reviews.text: The food is good - really good. Quality of produce is top rated. Very very fresh. You can choose various omakase options ... The dishes are very innovative
One of the best sushi restaurant I ever did. Great service, great food, great moment
Great food but expensive

the dinner was good- the aftermath worse- I woke up in the morning with stomach problems and vomited . I called the restaurant to let them know  and told them since we spent 2500 hkd for dinner a discount off what was paid  would be in duty. They called me back later to tell me they spoke with manager and would pay my "hospital"bills but nothing else. I told them luckily I didn't need to be hospitalised but they didn't seem to to care.  what apparently was high quality sushi turned into a gastro intestinal nightmare

Had high expectations but did not deliver; overpriced sushi and sashimi with rushed service...felt like they didn’t let us enjoy the dinner. The place tries to be upscale but felt cheated instead; USD$10 for literally one sushi roll...what a tourist trap!
